that I could have lost.

146
00:05:40,170 --> 00:05:42,720
I always think the best
tool I've got is my gut.

147
00:05:42,720 --> 00:05:44,910
You can usually tell if
something feels right.

148
00:05:44,910 --> 00:05:46,500
Most of the time I can.

149
00:05:46,500 --> 00:05:48,150
But I always like to top this up

150
00:05:48,150 --> 00:05:50,190
with some extra research as well.

151
00:05:50,190 --> 00:05:53,820
The other temptation to
avoid at all cost is debt.

152
00:05:53,820 --> 00:05:56,970
I fell into the equivalent
of $20,000 worth of debt

153
00:05:56,970 --> 00:05:58,140
in my younger days

154
00:05:58,140 --> 00:06:01,200
and lost so many years of
possible wealth building.

155
00:06:01,200 --> 00:06:04,080
The ones to really look
out for are payday loans.

156
00:06:04,080 --> 00:06:06,720
Payday loan companies are like predators.

157
00:06:06,720 --> 00:06:08,310
They see people wanting to keep up

158
00:06:08,310 --> 00:06:10,500
with their friends'
lifestyles on Instagram

159
00:06:10,500 --> 00:06:13,470
and they advertise to
them nonstop on Facebook,

160
00:06:13,470 --> 00:06:15,210
billboards, and newspapers,

161
00:06:15,210 --> 00:06:18,317
preying on their insecurities
and offering them quick money.

162
00:06:18,317 --> 00:06:20,092
Taking out one loan could lead you down

163
00:06:20,092 --> 00:06:22,470
a road of multiple months of debt,

164
00:06:22,470 --> 00:06:24,780
which is really, really hard to escape

165
00:06:24,780 --> 00:06:28,140
and can completely destroy
your investing journey.

166
00:06:28,140 --> 00:06:30,690
